# Index

Wiki entry portal. **The human comes in through 3-4 key points; agents (and you when you `/query`) then navigate via the domain hubs and `[[wikilinks]]`.** This file stays deliberately minimal — the detailed structure lives in the `wiki/domains/<d>.md` hubs.

## Overview

- [[overview]] — Portrait of {{name}}: background, role, areas of interest.
- [[radar]] — Open questions & points of attention. Check it in the morning.
- [[log]] — Chronological journal of wiki actions (ingest, query, save, lint, evolve).

## Domains

{{domains_index_section}}

---

Everything else (entities, concepts, sources, syntheses, cheatsheets, diagrams, decisions) is reachable via the domain hubs and `[[wikilinks]]`. This wiki follows the **tiered loading** pattern: every page carries a `summary_l0` (≤140 chars) and a `summary_l1` (2-5 sentences) in its frontmatter, letting an agent scan an entire domain without loading bodies. Cf. [[decisions/tiered-loading-wiki]].
